<p>I would just use numpy's <code>randn</code>:</p>

<pre><code>In [11]: df = pd.DataFrame(np.random.randn(100, 2))

In [12]: msk = np.random.rand(len(df)) &lt; 0.8

In [13]: train = df[msk]

In [14]: test = df[~msk]
</code></pre>

<p>And just to see this has worked:</p>

<pre><code>In [15]: len(test)
Out[15]: 21

In [16]: len(train)
Out[16]: 79
</code></pre>
